She ate soundly, her tiny paws working against the sides of the bottle like 
they would against mommy's side to get the milk out. Her itty claws clicked 
at the sides, feeling warmer when Starice spread her wings and cradled her 
in them.
The soft wings reminded her of mommy's fur and with the warm milk it was 
almost the exact same, the only things different is that the milk tasted 
different and she couldn't smell mommy's scent.
But she kept on eating, making little sucking sounds as she lowered the 
level of milk in the bottle.
The sounds of Starice's voice was comforting to her, soothing her with its 
sweet tone.
She was almost ready for sleep, and her paws left the bottle, moving slowly 
in tiny movements as she suckled.
So tiny, so soft and innocent. A round, rolly-polly puppy.
